# Portfolio Template Architecture — STRICT ENFORCEMENT

Pose & Poise offers custom site templates as a premium feature. This rule defines the architecture, naming conventions, and design principles for the template system.

## Two Distinct Systems

The platform consists of two separate but connected systems:

### 1. Main Application (Dashboard/Control Center)
- Landing page, onboarding, dashboard, settings, billing
- Uses brand colors: Cream (#FAF9F7), Charcoal (#1A1A1A), Camel (#C4A484)
- Uses brand fonts: Cormorant Garamond (headlines), Outfit (body)
- Authenticated users only
- Manages data, uploads, settings

### 2. Portfolio Templates (Public Mini-Sites)
- Rendered at `poseandpoise.studio/{username}`
- Each template is a self-contained 4-5 page mini-website
- Templates have their own color palettes, fonts, and layouts
- Public, no authentication required
- Read-only display of user data

## Template Naming Convention — REQUIRED

Templates use **conceptual alternative names** that evoke mood and industry focus:

| Template ID | Name | Target Aesthetic | Industry Focus |
|-------------|------|------------------|----------------|
| `elysian` | Elysian | Soft, warm, approachable | Commercial/Lifestyle |
| `obsidian` | Obsidian | Moody, high-contrast, edgy | Editorial/Fashion |
| `solstice` | Solstice | Dynamic, raw, powerful | Fitness/Athletic |
| `altar` | Altar | Minimalist, sophisticated, clean | Bridal/Luxury |

**FORBIDDEN:** Generic names like "Template 1", "Dark Theme", "Light Theme"

## Template Structure — REQUIRED

Each template lives in `/src/templates/{template-id}/`:

```
templates/
├── index.ts                    # Central registry & metadata
├── elysian/
